            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;My point is that the world &lt;i&gt;outside&lt;/i&gt; a corporation is entirely different from the world &lt;i&gt;inside.&lt;/i&gt;  If you are building an app that is accessible to the &quot;wooly wide web,&quot; and for general consumption by the public, then you have no choice but to roll your own authentication and authorization methods.  But, inside a corporation, where the only way to get there is to be there or to use VPN, then it is very likely that the application will not have  &lt;i&gt;must not&lt;/i&gt; have  &quot;its own&quot; methods for doing these things.  The app &lt;i&gt;must&lt;/i&gt; use these methods instead, to provide consistent, centralized management.&lt;/span&gt;

